cianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1108.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   49Shaman/51Mage Duo need suggestions for aquiring Mage gear</span><hr size=1> My Mage buddy has just recently come back to TZ from StormHammer but unfortunately left all his gear with an alt of his from a blue server and now has very little gear. I stripped my 29 wizzie and gave him some noob gear but it definitely needs to be upgraded. <br>
<br>
Now I know we could go farm HG's in RM for cash but that is a real pita on TZ because of PvP and we are both so sick of killing Geonids in CC that neither of us wants to go back. What I'm looking for mostly, are suggestions for quests and camp locations to upgrade virtually every item slot on the Mage. We don't mind killing greens as long as trivial loot code doesn't apply. I know almost nothing about Mage gear and he unfortunately has almost no time to search for stuff. Any help here would be greatly appreciated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zyphyr>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 710<br> <font color=#333333>(12/6/02 5:09:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1108.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 49Shaman/51Mage Duo need suggestions for aquiring Mage g</span><hr size=1> Without knowing about possible zone-control issues (since I don't play on TZ and have no clue as to what areas may be terminally unsafe for you to enter), or what your friend actually has:<br>
<br>
1) The (relatively recent) newbie zone quest armors are actually semi-decent.<br>
<br>
2)Great Oowomp (sp?) in TD. Drops batskull earrings and some other semi-usefull items.<br>
<br>
3)At least 3 slots (earring,bracer,ring) should be occupied by summoned foci and as such you don't need to fill them. Neck and Shoulder can be filled by foci until something better is aquired. Elemental Blanket makes a tolerable temporary back-slot.<br>
<br>
4)Pick up a Supple Scale Armband and a Kunzar Cloak(if the mage is of a race that can wear the cloak) in Karnor.<br>
<br>
5)Maiden's Eye : You probably won't be able to hunt here effectively, but there are several mage-only items that drop here and you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>might</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be able to pick up the 2 no-drop ones for free. On non-PvP servers, it is pretty much guaranteed that you could do so.<br>
<br>
6)The Hole. Hunt the elementals at the zone-in for Loam armor.<br>
<br>
7)1st 3 Coldain Prayer Shawl quests. Perhaps even #4. Beyond that, you start having to deal with Tailoring.... <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">Zyphyr Runnersbane</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44185&quot;">Vending Machine and Disciple of Zomm</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Darkblood<br>
Solusek Ro<br>
